cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CG, cs.GT 

The paper deals with approximation algorithms for solving linear systems, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA). It also involves the design of efficient data structures and algorithms for network flow problems (cs.DS), as well as the analysis of combinatorial and geometric structures (cs.DM). The use of preconditioners and iterative solvers is a common technique in computational geometry (cs.CG), and the paper presents a new algorithm for minimum-cost flow, which is a classic problem in graph theory (cs.GT).
